## 5. Database ŌĆö Current Schema by Feature Area

Migration filenames are listed for traceability. All migrations are idempotent unless noted.

### 5.1 Foundation / lazy-auth migration
- `migration_pre.sql`, `migration_pre_v2.sql` ŌĆö adds `legacy_appwrite_id` columns to `profiles`, `books`, `chapters`, `videos`, `comments`, `chapter_comments`, `posts` for idempotent dedup during the AppwriteŌåÆSupabase migration. Adds `posts.views_count`, ensures `profiles.bio` / `profiles.banner_url`.
- `migration_lazy_auth.sql` ŌĆö `profiles.email` with case-insensitive unique index, drops FK from `profiles.id ŌåÆ auth.users`, replaces `handle_new_user()` to claim a legacy profile by email on first sign-in.

### 5.2 Posts, comments, reactions
- Core tables `posts`, `comments`, `reactions` exist from earlier migrations.
- `migration_video_comments.sql` ŌĆö makes `comments` polymorphic across posts and videos (`post_id` OR `video_id` exclusive check), updates `notify_on_comment` trigger.
- `migration_video_reactions.sql` ŌĆö extends `notify_on_reaction` to handle videos (uses `videos.uploader_id`).
- `migration_video_comments_legacy.sql` / `migration_reactions_legacy.sql` ŌĆö allow comments and reactions on legacy (Appwrite) videos. `reactions.target_id` is `text` so it holds both UUIDs and Appwrite IDs; trigger try-casts and skips notification on legacy.

### 5.3 Books, chapters, reading
- `migration_books.sql` ŌĆö schema for `books`, `chapters`, `book_reads`, `book_bookmarks`, `book_likes`, `chapter_comments`. Storage bucket `book-covers` (public read, owner write). RLS publicly reads published chapters of public books only.
- `migration_books_fixup.sql` ŌĆö repoints book FKs to `profiles(id)` so PostgREST joins work correctly for the reader.
- `migration_book_like_bookmark_triggers.sql` ŌĆö auto-syncs `books.likes_count` from `book_likes` insert/delete.
- `migration_chapter_assets.sql` ŌĆö adds `chapters.cover_url` (chapter hero image). Inline images live in `chapters.content` HTML; storage path `book-covers/chapters/...`.
- `migration_chapter_scheduling.sql` ŌĆö adds `chapters.scheduled_publish_at`. RLS gates visibility on `(is_published AND (scheduled_publish_at IS NULL OR <= now()))`. RPC `publish_due_scheduled_chapters()` returns a count for diagnostic sweeps from the client; no state flip needed.

### 5.4 Videos
- `migration_video_bookmarks.sql` ŌĆö `video_bookmarks(user_id, video_id)`, RLS users-own.
- `migration_video_scheduling.sql` ŌĆö adds `videos.scheduled_publish_at`. Trigger `unhide_video_post_on_ready()` flips the linked `posts.is_hidden` when Bunny finishes encoding (skips if a future schedule is pending). RPC `publish_due_scheduled_videos()` for manual sweep.

### 5.5 Notifications
- `migration_notifications.sql` (Phase 1) ŌĆö `notifications` table + 7 engagement triggers + Realtime publication.
- `migration_notifications_phase2.sql` ŌĆö fan-out triggers for `posts insert ŌåÆ followers` (variants for new post / new video / repost) and `books ŌåÆ followers` on publish.
- `migration_notifications_phase3.sql` ŌĆö `@mention` regex detection in `comments` and `chapter_comments`, deduped vs. parent-thread/post-owner.
- `migration_notifications_coalesce.sql` ŌĆö adds `notifications.actor_ids[]` and rewrites engagement triggers to upsert via `upsert_engagement_notification()` (one unread row per `(recipient, type, target)`, actors deduped, capped at 20, `created_at` bumped). Follower fan-out stays uncoalesced.

### 5.6 Direct Messages
- `migration_dms.sql` (Phase 1) ŌĆö `conversations` + `messages` for 1:1 text. Canonical user ordering enforces a unique pair. Soft-delete via `deleted_at`. Realtime on `messages`.
- `migration_dms_phase2.sql` ŌĆö `message_reactions(message_id, user_id, emoji)`.
- `migration_dms_phase3.sql` ŌĆö group DMs + threading. Conversations gain `is_group`, `name`, `avatar_url`, `archived_by_*`, `muted_until_*`. Messages gain `reply_to_id`. New `conversation_participants` join table; RLS migrates to participant-based checks.
- `migration_dms_phase3_hotfix.sql` ŌĆö fixes RLS recursion by wrapping participant checks in a `SECURITY DEFINER` helper `is_conv_participant()`.
- `migration_dms_phase3_hotfix2.sql` ŌĆö bulletproofs the group-create RPC (dedupe + drop self + drop nulls).
- `migration_dms_phase4.sql` ŌĆö image attachments + GIFs: `messages.image_url`, `messages.image_kind ('upload'|'gif')`, body check relaxed to allow empty body if image present. Storage bucket `dm-attachments` (3MB ceiling, 2.5MB enforced client-side).
- `migration_dms_phase4_hotfix.sql` ŌĆö re-binds the body check constraint by introspecting `pg_constraint` (handles auto-naming inconsistency).
- `migration_dms_phase4_hotfix2.sql` ŌĆö temporarily drops `messages_notify` trigger (was flooding the bell).
- `migration_dms_phase4_hotfix3.sql` ŌĆö restores DM notifications with **per-conversation coalescing**: one unread `dm_message` row per conversation that bumps `created_at` + `metadata.preview` on each new message; `mark_conversation_read()` RPC also marks the related notification read so the bell badge clears.

### 5.7 Profile / social
- `migration_user_badges.sql` ŌĆö `user_badges(user_id, badge IN ('creator','writer','pioneer','verified','staff'))`. Public read, mod-only write. `grant_badge()` helper.
- `migration_pinned_posts.sql` ŌĆö `posts.pinned_at`, max 3 per user enforced by trigger. Profile feed orders `(pinned_at DESC NULLS LAST, created_at DESC)`.
- `migration_mutual_followers.sql` ŌĆö `get_mutual_followers(target, viewer, limit=12)` RPC for "Followed by alice, bob, +12 others" social-proof strip.

### 5.8 Moderation
- `migration_post_actions.sql` ŌĆö `post_hides`, `user_snoozes` (with expiry), `user_blocks` (bidirectional, unfollow on block), `post_reports` (reason enum, status pending/reviewing/resolved/dismissed).
- `migration_user_reports.sql` ŌĆö same shape, scoped to user-level reports.
- `migration_admin_setup.sql` ŌĆö adds `profiles.role ('user'|'moderator'|'admin')`, suspension + ban columns. Adds `posts.is_hidden` + `hidden_by` / `hidden_at` / `hidden_reason`. New `admin_actions` audit log (append-only). Helpers `is_moderator()`, `is_admin()`. View `posts_visible` filters banned + hidden.
- `migration_videos_books_perf.sql` ŌĆö extends moderation parity: `is_hidden` columns on `videos` and `books`, partial indexes, `videos_visible` + `books_visible` views.

### 5.9 Performance
- `migration_feed_perf.sql` ŌĆö composite + partial indexes for the feed, profile loads, hides, active snoozes. Runs `ANALYZE`.
- `migration_videos_books_perf.sql` ŌĆö see above.

