## 6. Edge Functions

| Function | Purpose | Env vars used |
|---|---|---|
| `bunny-upload` | Creates a Bunny Stream session and returns upload URL + GUID | `BUNNY_API_KEY_NEW`, `BUNNY_LIBRARY_ID_NEW`, `BUNNY_CDN_HOSTNAME_NEW` |
| `bunny-delete` | Deletes a Bunny video + Supabase row. Owner-checked. **Refuses to delete from the legacy library** (mobile-uploaded videos are DB-row-only deleted). | `BUNNY_API_KEY_NEW`, `BUNNY_LIBRARY_ID_NEW` |
| `bunny-webhook` | Bunny ŌåÆ Selebox callback. Maps Bunny status ŌåÆ `'ready'` / `'error'`, fetches duration on ready. JWT verification disabled. Verifies `VideoLibraryId` matches the new library before acting. | `BUNNY_API_KEY_NEW`, `BUNNY_LIBRARY_ID_NEW` |

The "old" Bunny env vars (`BUNNY_API_KEY`, `BUNNY_LIBRARY_ID`, `BUNNY_CDN_HOSTNAME`) are **parked in Supabase secrets** for any future migration tooling but are not referenced by these functions.

